up, ill educated’ (Latin  <i>male doctus</i>)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":40,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":49,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Mauduit II was born about 1175, in Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England, his father, Robert Mauduit I, was 19 and his mother, Agnes Mare, was 37. He married Beatrice de Murdac in 1220, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1245, in England, at the age of 71."},"et":{"about 1175–1245":"umbes 1175–1245","1175–1245":"1175–1245","1194–1221":"1194–1221","1221–1251":"1221–1251","1158–1191":"1158–1191","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1251":"1251","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1191":"1191","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1245":"1245","1221":"1221","about 1175":"umbes 1175","Warminster, Wiltshire, England":"Warminster, Wiltshire, England","Holgate, Shropshire, England":"Holdgate, Shropshire, England","Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England","Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England":"Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England","Somerford, Wiltshire, England, Great Britain":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1175–1245":"noin 1175–1245","1175–1245":"1175–1245","1194–1221":"1194–1221","1221–1251":"1221–1251","1158–1191":"1158–1191","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1251":"1251","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1191":"1191","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1245":"1245","1221":"1221","about 1175":"noin 1175","Warminster, Wiltshire, England":"Warminster, Wiltshire, England","Holgate, Shropshire, England":"Holdgate, Shropshire, England","Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England","Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England":"Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England","Somerford, Wiltshire, England, Great Britain":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1175–1245":"environ 1175–1245","1175–1245":"1175–1245","1194–1221":"1194–1221","1221–1251":"1221–1251","1158–1191":"1158–1191","1140–Female":"1140–Décédée","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1251":"1251","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1191":"1191","1180":"1180","1215":"1215",